# Automation Orchestration — Technical DAG UI

This module authors and observes immutable-versioned technical DAGs. Human
approvals and business state machines belong to workflow_automation.

## Contract first

- Read `contracts.ts` before editing any page, component, hook, or service.
- Import every DTO, request, filter, envelope, state union, and `ENDPOINTS`
  member from `contracts.ts`; never redefine an API shape in a component.
- Use recursive `JSONValue` for schema-driven data. `any`, `unknown`, and
  `Record<string, unknown>` casts are forbidden in this module.
- Never hardcode `/api/` paths. The sole prefix is
  `/api/v2/automation-orchestration` and all paths come from `ENDPOINTS`.

## Server and editor state

- TanStack Query owns server state, pagination, bounded polling, and retry.
- Draft graph edits remain local until an explicit save; preserve revision/ETag
  and surface conflicts rather than overwriting another editor.
- Published definitions and terminal execution evidence are always read-only.
- Node configuration is driven by the accessible registry descriptor schema.
  Missing or unentitled capabilities must render unavailable, never successful.

## Experience and accessibility

- Every page renders explicit skeleton, empty/filtered-empty, retryable error,
  permission-denied, submitting, and success states as applicable.
- All graph operations must have a keyboard-accessible alternative.
- Keep controls labelled, focus-visible, responsive, and WCAG 2.1 AA.

## Required checks

Run TypeScript, ESLint with zero warnings, module tests, accessibility tests,
and the production build after every coherent edit.
